snippet.textDisplay: Fun fact about pepsi: in Claremont, NC there is a park where Pepsi used to be bottled. In the City Park there once stood a rock building approximately 75 feet long and 25 feet wide. This was the Claremont Pepsi Cola Bottling Company. The spring is still active that furnished the water for the cola Ingredients used in the production of the cola were ale, water, flavoring, extracts, white sugar, and syrup.

snippet.textDisplay: Idk wtf type of Heads up 7 up yall played, but mine WAS a game. 7 people were chosen and went to the front. Everyone else put their heads down and put their thumbs up. The 7 would sneak around and each tap someone’s thumb, then return to the front. They’d all say “Heads up 7 up” and everyone lifted their heads and the 7 that were chosen had to stand up. Aka HEADS UP 7 UP. The chosen ones had to guess who tapped their thumb. If you got it right, you became one of the 7 and the person that chose you would sit down. Rinse and repeat.

snippet.textDisplay: Heads up 7 up is a game. You have seven pickers and everyone else puts their heads down and thumbs up. The pickers pick people by touching their thumbs and then someone “usually the teacher, aka me” says “heads up 7 up” and the people picked stand up and try to guess who picked them. It’s a game I sometimes play with my seventh graders when we have five extra minutes and I don’t want them to be on their phones. We don’t play it a lot though, because by seventh grade they’re kind of over it.
